column28: Through legislation and social code, modern-day Nigeria has become a hostile and dangerous country for queer people. As a queer person of the Nigerian diaspora, I struggle to hold both my “queer” and “Nigerian” identities because they seem contradictory . In this paper , I detail my journey reckoning with these two seemingly dissonant parts of my identity .
